inclusion.criterion: Able to provide informed consent in English
inclusion.label: met

exclusion.criterion: Received treatment of cervical dysplasia with LEEP, cone biopsy, laser procedure or cryotherapy within THREE years
exclusion.label: unknown

exclusion.criterion: Received colposcopy of cervix within TWO years
exclusion.label: not_met

exclusion.criterion: Received Pap test within ONE year
exclusion.label: not_met

exclusion.criterion: Immunocompromised (positive human immunodeficiency virus [HIV] test, transplant recipient, received chemotherapy for cancer, or taking immunosuppressant drugs)
exclusion.label: unknown

exclusion.criterion: Decisionally impaired adults requiring a legally authorized representative
exclusion.label: not_met

notes: A 54-year-old woman with abnormal cervical squamous intraepithelial/glandular lesion and HPV 16 positivity, who smokes and drinks alcohol frequently.
